# Cloudflare Pages security headers
# https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/headers/
#
# Notes (2026-05-19):
# - HSTS: 6-month max-age, NO preload, NO includeSubDomains yet.
#   Per Sally's review: preload is hard to roll back (browser-baked list),
#   and includeSubDomains can break any *.michaelreflects.com subdomain
#   that isn't HTTPS-only. Revisit both after 6+ months of stable HSTS.
# - X-Frame-Options: DENY (no one needs to embed this in a frame).
# - Permissions-Policy: deny features the site never uses, including the
#   privacy-hostile FLoC interest-cohort.
# - CSP intentionally omitted from this pass — will be added in
#   Content-Security-Policy-Report-Only mode in a follow-up commit
#   once we've mapped every third-party script (Font Awesome kit,
#   Tinylytics, GLightbox, Webmention.io, YouTube/Vimeo embeds,
#   Cloudflare email obfuscation injection, theme-toggle inline scripts).

/*
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=15552000
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Permissions-Policy: accelerometer=(), camera=(), geolocation=(), gyroscope=(), magnetometer=(), microphone=(), payment=(), usb=(), interest-cohort=()
